\f1\b\fs28 \cf3 \strokec3 Step 1: The Foundation\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa160\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0\fs24 \cf3 The script immediately updates the Pi and installs every necessary core package.\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sa160\partightenfactor0
\ls1\ilvl0\cf3 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec3 It purges \cf4 \cb5 \strokec4 modemmanager\cf3 \cb1 \strokec3  and \cf4 \cb5 \strokec4 brltty\cf3 \cb1 \strokec3  (these default Linux packages notoriously hijack USB serial ports and block Arduinos).\
\ls1\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec3 It downloads Python, FFmpeg (for video), Apache2 (for web routing), and the tunneling tools (Ngrok and FRP).\
\ls1\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec3 It grants your \cf4 \cb5 \strokec4 drone\cf3 \cb1 \strokec3  user absolute permission to access the GPIO pins and video hardware.\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \strokec2 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa80\partightenfactor0

\f1\b\fs28 \cf3 \strokec3 Step 2: The Traffic Cop (Apache Reverse Proxy)\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa160\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0\fs24 \cf3 You have multiple Python scripts running on different network ports. If you tried to expose all of them through an internet tunnel, it would fail.\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sa160\partightenfactor0
\ls2\ilvl0\cf3 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec3 Apache acts as the front door on standard Port \cf4 \cb5 \strokec4 80\cf3 \cb1 \strokec3 .\
\ls2\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec3 When a command comes in, Apache looks at the URL and seamlessly forwards it to the correct hidden background script.\

