\f1\b\fs28 \cf3 \strokec3 Step 3: The Video Engine (\cf4 \cb5 \strokec4 camera.py\cf3 \cb1 \strokec3 )\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa160\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0\fs24 \cf3 This writes a lightweight Python script dedicated entirely to video.\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sa160\partightenfactor0
\ls3\ilvl0\cf3 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec3 It uses \cf4 \cb5 \strokec4 ffmpeg\cf3 \cb1 \strokec3  to physically grab the \cf4 \cb5 \strokec4 /dev/video0\cf3 \cb1 \strokec3  hardware stream at 30 frames per second.\
\ls3\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec3 It wraps the video frames in a standard HTTP multipart response so your web browser can view the live feed with practically zero latency.\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \strokec2 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa80\partightenfactor0

\f1\b\fs28 \cf3 \strokec3 Steps 4-8: The Master Brain (\cf4 \cb5 \strokec4 pilot.py\cf3 \cb1 \strokec3 )\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa160\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0\fs24 \cf3 This is the core nervous system. It writes the massive Python script that acts as the bridge between your web browser and the physical microcontrollers.\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sa160\partightenfactor0
\ls4\ilvl0
\f1\b \cf3 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec3 Auto-Discovery:
\f0\b0  It rapidly sweeps all USB ports, shouting \cf4 \cb5 \strokec4 PING_ID\cf3 \cb1 \strokec3  to find out which cable connects to the UNO and which connects to the ESP.\
\ls4\ilvl0
\f1\b \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec3 Multi-Threading:
\f0\b0  It runs the GPS, the UNO drive logic, the ESP steering logic, and the web interface simultaneously on separate processor threads so a delay in the video doesn't crash the steering.\
\ls4\ilvl0
\f1\b \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec3 Privilege Escalation:
\f0\b0  It contains the logic to seamlessly pipe your SSH root password (\cf4 \cb5 \strokec4 drone786@@\cf3 \cb1 \strokec3 ) directly into the Linux kernel to execute \cf4 \cb5 \strokec4 poweroff\cf3 \cb1 \strokec3  or \cf4 \cb5 \strokec4 reboot\cf3 \cb1 \strokec3  without prompting the user.\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \strokec2 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa80\partightenfactor0

\f1\b\fs28 \cf3 \strokec3 Step 9: The Frontend (\cf4 \cb5 \strokec4 hud.html\cf3 \cb1 \strokec3 )\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa160\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0\fs24 \cf3 The script creates the \cf4 \cb5 \strokec4 templates\cf3 \cb1 \strokec3  folder and writes your entire HTML, CSS, and JavaScript interface.\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sa160\partightenfactor0
\ls5\ilvl0\cf3 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec3 This file contains the dual-joystick math, the Leaflet mapping logic for the GPS, and all the settings modals.\
\ls5\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec3 It constantly fetches \cf4 \cb5 \strokec4 /data\cf3 \cb1 \strokec3  from the Python backend to keep your battery, ping, and speed metrics perfectly synced in real-time.\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \strokec2 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa80\partightenfactor0

\f1\b\fs28 \cf3 \strokec3 Steps 10.5 & 10.8: Network Failsafes\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa160\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0\fs24 \cf3 If you take the drone to an empty parking lot, it won't have Wi-Fi.\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sa160\partightenfactor0
\ls6\ilvl0
\f1\b \cf4 \cb5 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec4 drone_ap.sh\cf3 \cb1 \strokec3 :
\f0\b0  This script checks if the Pi is connected to the internet. If 50 seconds pass with no connection, it forces the Pi's internal Wi-Fi chip to broadcast its own network (\cf4 \cb5 \strokec4 DRONE_SETUP\cf3 \cb1 \strokec3 ).\
\ls6\ilvl0
\f1\b \cf4 \cb5 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec4 keepalive.sh\cf3 \cb1 \strokec3 :
\f0\b0  Mobile phone hotspots often go to sleep if they don't see active traffic. This script pings Google every 3 seconds to keep the connection wide awake.\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \strokec2 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa80\partightenfactor0

\f1\b\fs28 \cf3 \strokec3 Step 10: Tunnels & Automation\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa160\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0\fs24 \cf3 This configures how you access the drone from anywhere in the world.\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sa160\partightenfactor0
\ls7\ilvl0\cf3 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec3 It configures \cf4 \cb5 \strokec4 msmtp\cf3 \cb1 \strokec3  so the drone can automatically send emails using your Gmail app password.\
\ls7\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
